    </div>
    <div class="card-body">
        <blockquote class="blockquote mb-0">
            <p>
                <ul>
                    <li>
                        ESWL (Extracorporeal Shock Wave Lithotripsy)
                        It uses shock waves to break Kidney stones into small pieces that can move through the urinary tract & pass from the body.
                    </li>
                    <li>
                        URS (Ureteroscopy)
                        In this, the ureteroscope is passed through the urethra and into the ureter to remove a stone using the laser.
                    </li>
                    <li>
                        RIRS (Retrograde Intrarenal Surgery)
                        It is a procedure for doing surgery within the kidney using a flexible ureteroscope to remove upper ureter and small kidney stones.
                    </li>
                    <li>
                        PCNL (Percutaneous Nephrolithotomy)
                        It is a minimally invasive procedure in which large kidney stones are removed through a small incision in skin.
                    </li>
                </ul>
            </p>
        </blockquote>
